"title": "4290: valleys",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4290",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Valleys used as places of permanent settlement</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:17\">GEN 26:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:25\">NUM 14:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh17:16\">JOS 17:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:28\">JDG 18:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:14-1Chr12:15\">1CH 12:14–12:15</a></p>\n<h2>Valleys as places for camp-sites</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:33\">JDG 6:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:10-Num21:12\">NUM 21:10–21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:29\">DEU 3:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:8-Judg7:12\">JDG 7:8–7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:15\">1CH 11:15</a></p>\n<h2>Valleys used for pasture and crops</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr4:39-1Chr4:40\">1CH 4:39–4:40</a></strong> <em>Palestine was noted as a dry land, but valleys provided the necessary moisture for pastures and crop growth.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:29\">1CH 27:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:13\">PSA 65:13</a></p>\n<h2>Valleys used for battles</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:8\">GEN 14:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:7-Josh11:8\">JOS 11:7–11:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:1-1Sam17:3\">1SA 17:1–17:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:13\">2SA 8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:11-2Chr25:12\">2CH 25:11–25:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:7\">2KI 14:7</a></p>\n<h2>Valleys as places of worship and sacrifice</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:3\">2CH 28:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:1-Deut21:9\">DEU 21:1–21:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:25-2Chr20:26\">2CH 20:25–20:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:23-Jer2:25\">JER 2:23–2:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:35\">JER 32:35</a></p>\n<h2>Valleys on the day of the LORD</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:5\">ISA 22:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic1:3-Mic1:4\">MIC 1:3–1:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:3-Zech14:5\">ZEC 14:3–14:5</a></p>\n<h2>The metaphorical use of valleys</h2>\n<h3>The valley of death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:4\">PSA 23:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:32-Job21:33\">JOB 21:32–21:33</a></p>\n<h3>The valley of decision</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:14\">JOL 3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:1-Joel3:2\">JOL 3:1–3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:12\">JOL 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>The valley of dry bones</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:1-Ezek37:14\">EZK 37:1–37:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The levelling of valleys as a preparation for the coming of the Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:4-Luke3:5\">LUK 3:4–3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:3-Isa40:4\">ISA 40:3–40:4</a></p>\n<h2>The Valley of Hinnom</h2>\n<h3>The Valley of Hinnom as part of the boundary between Judah and Benjamin, lying to the south of Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:8\">JOS 15:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:16\">JOS 18:16</a></p>\n<h3>The Valley of Hinnom as a place of child sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:3\">2CH 28:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:35\">JER 32:35</a></p>\n<h3>The Valley of Hinnom as a place of God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:30-Jer7:32\">JER 7:30–7:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:1-Jer19:15\">JER 19:1–19:15</a></p>\n<h2>The Kidron Valley</h2>\n<h3>The Kidron Valley as a boundary of Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:36-1Kgs2:37\">1KI 2:36–2:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:23\">2SA 15:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:38-Jer31:40\">JER 31:38–31:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:1\">JHN 18:1</a></p>\n<h3>The Kidron Valley as a place for the destruction of pagan cult objects</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:11-1Kgs15:13\">1KI 15:11–15:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:4-2Kgs23:6\">2KI 23:4–23:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:3-2Chr34:4\">2CH 34:3–34:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:12\">2KI 23:12</a></p>\n<h3>The Kidron Valley in prophetic visions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:1-Ezek47:8\">EZK 47:1–47:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:1-Joel3:2\">JOL 3:1–3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:8\">ZEC 14:8</a></p>",
